elf of its nonperformance. Ms. Gold made it impossible for Mr. Gold to perform his obligations to the partnership by refusing to participate in the operations of the company."},{"name":"Truth","raw_text":"Mr. Gold made statements about Ms. Gold that were truthful, and therefore not defamatory."}]},{"claim_id":"9cf9c06a-36a1-4e81-80ef-a886ad6ff085","raw_texts":["BREACH OF CONTRACT AND LIBEL"],"damages":{"compensatory":["$50,000 total damages claimed","Damages for slandering reputation","Payment for taking 80% of the business","Damages for threatening plaintiff and family"],"punitive":[],"statutory":[],"equitable":[],"other":["Such other and further relief as the court may deem proper","Attorney's fees","Costs of suit"]},"defenses":[{"name":"Unclean Hands","raw_text":"Plaintiff has engaged in inequitable behavior, including fraud, deceit, unconscionability, and bad faith relating to their claim."},{"name":"Setoff","raw_text":"Any damages award to Plaintiff/Counter-Defendant must be set off with any damages awarded to Defendant/Counter-Plaintiff stemming from the various counts."},{"name":"Abandonment","raw_text":"Ms. Gold abandoned her responsibilities to the partnership."},{"name":"Prior Breach","raw_text":"Ms. Gold unjustifiably refused to perform her agreement in who or in any substantial part, allowing Mr. Gold to rescind the partnership agreement, which he did within a reasonable time, and provided Ms. Gold her rightful share of the proceeds of the sale of inventory."},{"name":"Discharge by Material Breach","raw_text":"Ms. Gold materially breached her agreement with Mr. Gold, thereby discharging Mr. Gold from his obligations thereunder."},{"name":"Prevention of Performance","raw_text":"One who prevents or makes impossible the performance or happening of a condition precedent upon which his liability by the terms of a contract is made to depend cannot avail himself of its nonperformance. Ms. Gold made it impossible for Mr. Gold to perform his obligations to the pa